'''Charlie Vickers''' is an Australian actor. He has portrayed [[Halbrand]] (later revealed to be [[Sauron]] himself) in the [[Amazon Studios]] television series ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Rings of Power]]''.<ref>{{webcite|author=|articleurl=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt9788618/fullcredits|articlename=Full Cast & Crew|dated=|website=IMDb|accessed=31 July 2022}}</ref> He was unaware about the character’s true identity until the filming of the [[Adar (episode)|third episode]].<ref>{{webcite|author=|articleurl=https://www.wionews.com/entertainment/the-rings-of-power-actor-charlie-vickers-reveals-that-even-he-didnt-know-he-was-sauron-525630 |articlename=The Rings of Power' actor Charlie Vickers reveals that even he didn't know he was Sauron|dated=15 October 2022|website=wionews.com|accessed=26 October 2022}}</ref>

==Quotes==
{{quote|It is nice. I've been having to carry this for quite a long time. It's nice to just be like, it's out. Now it's out.|Charlie Vickers, Screen Rant}}
{{quote|A lot of the subconscious work was a creating a human life for Halbrand. In order for Sauron to effectively portray Halbrand and deceive people, I think he would have to have a pretty comprehensive life mapped out. I guess all the subconscious work I did was in creating that and then also creating Sauron’s life and really thinking about where he’s come from. It’s a lot of reading, but also a lot of practical things. We were so lucky in New Zealand to have the country. So I went hiking for a long time to create Sauron’s world. I went to Tongariro National Park, which is [what] they used for Mount Doom in The Fellowship of the Ring, the original trilogy. So the subconscious work was all kind of there. And I hope that it informed the performance — I kept that in my mind as we were going|Charlie Vickers, Polygon}}

